                            <comment id="13948438" author="amatsukawa" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 20:48:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch directly uses a murmur hash seeded with 0 to remove this version dependency on guava.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13948593" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 22:51:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=amatsukawa&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;amatsukawa&quot;&gt;Akihiro Matsukawa&lt;/a&gt;, thank you for the patch. But it breaks the compilation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    [javac] /Users/cheolsoop/workspace/pig-apache/src/org/apache/pig/newplan/logical/relational/LogicalPlan.java:130: cannot find symbol
    [javac] symbol  : method murmur_32(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)
    [javac] location: class com.google.common.hash.Hashing
    [javac]         HashFunction hf = Hashing.murmur_32(0);
    [javac]                                  ^
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Did you mean &lt;tt&gt;murmur3_32(int)&lt;/tt&gt;? I see it in JavaDoc &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.guava-libraries.googlecode.com/git-history/v11.0/javadoc/com/google/common/hash/Hashing.html#murmur3_32(int)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13948623" author="amatsukawa" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 23:11:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch should have said &quot;murmur3_32&quot; instead of &quot;murmur_32&quot;. Fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13948640" author="cheolsoo" created="Wed, 26 Mar 2014 23:24:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1. I&apos;ll commit it tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thank you Akihiro!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
